      <div class="msgContentFrame">Additionally, it's not about killing stuff quickly, it's about killing it well. <br /> <br />If you were able to kill a red mob in three hits, you would be missing out on the SP. I've found that a little management of the fight yields the most sp. Currently getting 500sp (divided between sword and shield) every fight, with each fight lasting approximately 2 minutes. <br /> <br />By management, I mean - control the fight, attack at the right times with the right skills, keep your guard up etc. etc. If you play the back-foot then you'll yield less sp than if you're forcing the mob to play your game. Sorry if this doesn't make sense. <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Chelsea Pride <br />Rabanastre <br />Currahee Linkshell <br />BTN: 25 MNR: 18 CON: 20 <br /><a href="http://www.guildwork.com/ffxiv/rabanastre/chelsea-pride/" title="http://www.guildwork.com/ffxiv/rabanastre/chelsea-pride/" rel="external nofollow">http://www.guildwork.com/ffxiv/rabanastre/chelsea-pride/</a></div></div>
